ZCZC GE79
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND
COASTGUARD AGENCY AT 122300 UTC
A RIDGE AXIS LOCATED IN THE MID ATLANTIC ON SUNDAY
EVENING WILL MOV EWARDS TO LIE ACROSS THE UK BY THE END
OF MONDAY. A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE WILL DEVELOP TO
THE W OF ICELAND LATER WITH LOW PRESSURE OVER EUROPE AND
THE MEDITERRANEAN SEA. THE RIDGE AXIS WILL DECLINE TO LIE
IN NERN EUROPE BY THE END OF TUESDAY WITH AREAS OF LOW
PRESSURE NEAR ICELAND. A FRONTAL TROUGH WILL THEN EXTEND
SWARDS ACROSS THE UK ON WEDNESDAY. DURING SUNDAY EVENING
AND MONDAY N OR NE WINDS WILL BE STRG OCNL GALE BUT
DECR IN NERN SEA AREAS LATER ON MONDAY AND DECR TO OCNL
STRG IN THE S. WINDS WILL CONTINUE TO MOD IN THE S BUT
BECMG STRG S WITH GALES IN NERN SEA AREAS ON TUESDAY
PERHAPS SEV GALES LATER IN VIKING AND FAIR ISLE. ON
WEDNESDAY WINDS WILL SLWY DECREASE TO OCNL STRG IN THE N
SEA WITH OCCASIONAL GALES IN FAIR ISLE
